    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "deviceClass": "Class III"
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credible",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis predictions are sufficiently credible for VAD regulatory submission",
      "description": "The CFD model predicts absolute hemolysis index values for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump within an acceptable uncertainty envelope across all five flow-speed operating points specified in the COU. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrates that predicted hemolysis indices remain below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.8 g/100 L with 95% confidence. The claim encompasses model form adequacy for the power-law hemolysis constitutive relation, mesh-independent spatial resolution verified at three refinement levels, and temporal convergence confirmed for all pulsatile operating conditions. Scope is limited to the five COU-specified operating points; extrapolation beyond the validated envelope is excluded.",
      "purpose": "Support regulatory decision that the CFD model provides sufficient evidence of hemolysis safety for a Class III VAD submission to FDA under the 510(k) De Novo pathway.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; five operating points (3 L/min at 2500 RPM, 4 L/min at 2500 RPM, 5 L/min at 3000 RPM, 6 L/min at 3500 RPM, 7 L/min at 4000 RPM); power-law hemolysis model with Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients."
    }
  ],
