    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that despite gaps in multiple credibility factors, the combination of PIV velocity validation, Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification demonstrating 95th-percentile NIH below the clinical threshold, and GCI-confirmed mesh adequacy provides sufficient evidence to accept the CFD model for regulatory submission. The orphan claim binding this package asserts overall model credibility but does not carry a structured derivation link to the underlying evidence nodes — a subtle epistemic gap that the weakener-detection system should flag as W-EP-01.",
